import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    sns.histplot(data=data, x='Miles_per_Gallon', kde=True)
    plt.axvline(data['Miles_per_Gallon'].median(), color='red', linestyle='--', label=f"Median: {data['Miles_per_Gallon'].median():.2f}")
    plt.title("What is the distribution of Miles_per_Gallon?", wrap=True)
    plt.legend()
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['Year'] = pd.to_datetime(data['Year'], errors='coerce')
    data = data[pd.notna(data['Year'])]
    data['Year'] = data['Year'].dt.year

    plt.figure(figsize=(10, 6))
    ax = sns.countplot(x='Year', data=data, palette='viridis')
    plt.title('What is the distribution of Year?', wrap=True)
    plt.xlabel('Year')
    plt.ylabel('Count')
    plt.xticks(rotation=45)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
